    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-05-15T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-05-15T16:00:00-05:00" n="276"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d276">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.77/78a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FDR1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Francis</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-05-15T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 15, 1917, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1404. The following Advisory Commission of Railway Experts to Russia has been
                    appointed: <persName corresp="#p_SJF1">John F. Stevens</persName>, chairman;
                        <persName>John G. Greiner</persName>, <persName>George Gibbs</persName>,
                        <persName>W. L. Darling</persName>, <persName>Henry Miller</persName>,
                    members; accompanied by <persName>Franklin Reading</persName>, secretary and
                    disbursing officer; <persName>Edward P. Shannon</persName>, secretary;
                        <persName>C. A. Decker</persName>, stenographer; <persName>Eugene C.
                        Stevens</persName>, clerk; <persName>Leslie R. Fellows</persName>,
                    stenographer.</p>
                <p>They sailed on the 14th instant from Vancouver by the <hi rend="italic">Empress
                        of India</hi> and will arrive at Vladivostok.</p>
                <p>Advise Government in order that proper instructions may be sent to Russian
                    authorities at Vladivostok.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
